   # Tulum Discovery - Web MVP

   This is a Next.js 14 Progressive Web App for Tulum tourism.

   ## Tech Stack
   - Next.js 14 (App Router)
   - TypeScript (strict mode)
   - Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
   - Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth)
   - Mapbox GL JS for maps
   - Google Places API for venues
   - Claude API for AI itinerary

   ## Project Goals
   - Build web MVP first (8 weeks)
   - Launch as PWA (installable)
   - Only build native apps if validated

   ## Core Features (MVP)
   Week 1-2: Foundation (map, weather, venue browsing)
   Week 3-4: Venue details, Google Places integration
   Week 5-6: AI itinerary planner, user auth
   Week 7: Events calendar, basic messaging
   Week 8: Business portal, PWA setup, launch

   ## Coding Standards
   - Use Server Components by default
   - Client Components only when needed ('use client')
   - Never expose API keys in client code
   - Mobile-first responsive design
   - Tailwind utility classes (no custom CSS)
   - All API routes in /app/api/*
   - Components in /components
   - Utilities in /lib

   ## File Organization
   /app - Next.js pages and API routes
   /components - Reusable UI components
   /lib - Utilities, API clients, types
   /public - Static assets
   